Topic LIAS: Prevent duplicate submodel imports in control files when the same submodel type is used multiple times (method `get_controlfileheader` of class `Model` of module `modeltools`) and support saving control files of models that rely on vectorial submodels (method `save_controls` of class `Model` of module `modeltools`).
Topic LIAS: Add the property `collectives` to class `HydPy` of module `hydpytools` and use it for determining the correct device and method orders for simulation.

Topic LIAS: Add the argument `no_connect` (defaults to True) to all private "connect" methods of class `Model` of module `modeltools` to allow defining models that cannot always build the required connections and add the required argument `position` to method `_connect_subgroup` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` to enforce that the relevant node sequences are either connected with the corresponding model sequences of the first or the last submodel (this approach is very debatable but at least works for now).

Topic LIAS: Let class `IntegrationTest` of module `testtools` cope with cases where the defined elements belong to a collective.

Possible alternatives are to let the model developer pass all these elements himself or provide the overarching element himself.  We need more use cases to see which approach is best, so I stick to the chosen one for now.

Topic LIAS: Support handling the initial conditions of multiple submodels of the same type in integration tests (class `IntegrationTest` of module `testtools`).

Using the sequence's ID as a name suffix makes them hardly usable in doctests. We may need to come up with a smarter solution later.

Topic LIAS: Write all sequence aliases into a single file (`aliases.py`) because the old separation into `inputs.py` and `outputs.py` became misleading (see the next point) and obsolete (see the second next point).

From now on, aliases for all inlet, outlet, and sender sequences are also available.  Also, a sequence's group is now part of its alias name, which avoids name collisions.

Topic LIAS: Support writing of control files for cases where multiple `SubmodelAdder` instances allow adding submodels following different interfaces to the same Submodel(s)Property object (module `modeltools`).
Topic LIAS: Improve the cythonization of model equations regarding casting to unions of submodel interfaces.

Topic LIAS: Add the `deploymode` versions `oldsim_bi`, `obs_bi`, and `obs_oldsim_bi` to allow the use of discharge measurements as lower boundary conditions for hydrodynamical routing models like LIAS.
Topic LIAS: Ensure that model methods `load_data`, `save_data`, and `new2obs` are also called for all submodels when working in Cython mode (module `modelutils`).
Topic LIAS: Ensure that the model method `new2obs` is also called for all submodels when working in pure Python mode (module `modeltools`).
Topic LIAS: Add the `sw1d` base model.
Topic LIAS: Add the alias `l1` for `Literal[1] to module `typingtools`.
Topic LIAS: Add the "user model" model `sw1d_channel`.
Topic LIAS: Add the "composite model" `sw1d_network`.

Topic LIAS: Add the routing submodel `sw1d_lias`, which implements a 1-dimensional version of the "local inertial approximation of the shallow water equations" introduced by Bates (2010) and "stabilised" by Almeida (2012).
Topic LIAS: Add the routing submodel `sw1d_q_in` for inserting "longitudinal" inflow into the first segment of a channel.
Topic LIAS: Add the routing submodel `sw1d_q_out` for removing "longitudinal" outflow from the last segment of a channel.
Topic LIAS: Add the routing submodel `sw1d_q_weir` calculating "longitudinal" outflow from the last segment of a channel as free flow over a weir after Poleni.
Topic LIAS: Add the storage submodel `sw1d_storage`, which calculates a single channel segment's water balance and level.
Extend the dictionary-based approach for handling initial conditions to the submodel concept.
Fix a typo in the exception messages raised by class `SubmodelAdder` of module `importtools` when submodel adding failed.
Couple each submodel with the element of its main model to improve error messages (property `model` of class `Element` of module `devicetools`).
Fix a few doctest of the base models  `evap` and `lland`, which were not regularly executed before due to a recently fixed bug in the doctest adding mechanism in the context of adding submodels.
Document all available submodel interfaces' `typeid` attributes (subpackage `interfaces`).
Document the "new type" `Name` defined in module `typingtools`.
Document the "new type" `ID` defined in module `servertools`.

Let function `check_selectedvariables` of module `testtools` explicitly avoid considering the "mathematical Cython wrappers" provided by module `modelutils` as variables.

The concrete occasion is to avoid mistaking `modelutils.inf` and `flu.inflow` in method `Calc_MaxTimeStep_V2` of base model `sw1d`.
Update the docstring of function `autodoc_applicationmodel` of module `autodoctools`.
Let function `check_methodorder` of module `testtools` ignore all additional and interface methods.
Exclude `pass` statements from code coverage analysis for exhaustiveness checking and because `...` is already skipped (so far, for function overloading).

Minor fixes to module `itemtools`.

 * Complete 2e52e67855ea9a1bc6357258527b1d5b0d1439e5 regarding switching fro `objecttools.assert_never` to `typing.assert_never` (revealed by commit 3bac1932c021342fc6fff7d48f0107c12e3e6e93).
 * Add a missing doctest to method `collect_variables` of class `ChangeItem` of module `itemtools` (also revealed by commit 3bac1932c021342fc6fff7d48f0107c12e3e6e93, but for unknown reasons...).
 * Correct a few typos.

Improve the handling of the attribute `deviceorder` of class `HydPy` of module `hydpytools`.

 * Turn it into a read-only property that returns a tuple instead of a least for safety.
 * Add the `silent` flag to method `update_devices` (primarily) to avoid crashes when reading network files that define `collectives`.

Add a `pragma: no cover` statement to a `continue` line in method `_connect_subgroup` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` for which `coveragepy` otherwise reports missing coverage.

Due to CPython's peephole optimizer, see https://github.com/nedbat/coveragepy/issues/198.
Add the application model `sw1d_lias_sluice`, which extends the routing submodel `sw1d_lias` with simple sluice functionalities.
Update some docstrings in module `dam_control`, which still mentioned artificial neural networks instead of the now-used general interpolators.

Translate the Python source code of all models into `pyx` and `pxd` Cython files.

This commit should not change the current functionalities of HydPy or its models in any way.  However, it enables us to "cimport" cythonized models, which we will use later to offer framework users ways to define cythonizable callback functions.

Modify 7f9a8fe26fd4e1f4a731570d77a6d65a8829fe87 by connecting receiver nodes with the last instead of the first submodel within a submodel vector.

The new version appears more symmetric with the handling of outlet nodes and is the right thing for letting a receiver node provide its "downstream" water levels to an instance of the new application model `sw1d_gate_out`.
Add a `CallbackWrapper` to each cythonized model to later allow users to define callback functions executed by the respective model (module `modelutils`).

Convert the methods `compile_` and `move_dll` from class `Cythonizer` to module `modelutils` functions.

This refactoring step makes the relevant functionalities easily accessible for compiling callback functions.

Add class `CallbackParameter` to module `parametertools` for defining parameters whose values are modifyable by user-defined callback functions.

This commit makes everything workable in the pure Python mode but does not address cythonization.
Add the model-specific functionalities to method `parameters` of class `PyxWriter` of module `modelutils` required for working with `CallbackParameter` instances in Cython mode.
Add the method `get_callbackmodule` to module `modelutils`, which creates or updates the required cython module containing the user-defined callback function on the fly.
Do not load the automatically cythonized callback functions into the `hydpy.cythons` namespace because we want to handle them "more private" for now (and think about storing them elsewhere later).
Add Cython as a requirement and to the Windows installer to support the cythonization of user-defined callables.
Add the `sw1d_gate_out` routing submodel for calculating "longitudinal" outflow from the last segment of a channel as the flow under a submerged gate.
Add Python's `include` and `libs` directories into the Windows installer to enable cythonizing callback functions.
Add the "smooth" filter function `filter_norm` to the Cython extension module `smoothutils`.
Use the `filter_norm` function of module `smoothutils` to prevent oscillations that the `sw1d_gate_out` model may introduce due to relying on method `Calc_Discharge_V3`.
Let method `save_conditions` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` properly write condition files of models that handle submodel vectors via `SubmodelsProperty` instances.
Update the copyright shown in the online documentation.
Update the online documentation regarding the supported Python versions (now 3.8 to 3.11).

Add the `None` return type annotation to all `__call__` methods and use class `Property` of module `propertytools` instead of the built-in `property` for defining the `shape` attribute of all `Variable` subclasses.

We recently discovered some incompatibilities with older numpy versions.  The changes in this commit helped Mypy find the critical code sections so we could fix them.

Refresh the deployment from AppVeyor to PyPI.

The password had changed.  From now on, we work with a token instead.

(cherry picked from commit 2d47c2a39b56103c07bfebd2cc76e6caf20740b2)

Update the token for sending AppVeyor artefacts to GitHub Releases.

(cherry picked from commit 398d7d54f1f895fac05a42fa9be8201c7a77dbb1)
Improve the documentation of method `Return_AdjustedWindSpeed_V1` of base model `evap`.
Remove the `reprcomments` option from class `Options` of module `optiontools`, which was not well supported likely never used by anyone.
Adjust two type hints to Matplotlib 3.8.0.

Set the lower `SPAN` value of the state sequences `SDG1`, `SDG2`, and `SBG` of base model `lland` to `None` because they can become negative due to evaporation from river or lake surfaces (fixes 8d55d2b4fb8e94dda64712f630ae0f8f26bcb656).
Fix a typo in one of the basic equations of method `Calc_SoilHeatFlux_V1` of base model `evap`.
Replace the remaining `d_` prefix from some method-internal type declarations of the `evap` base model by explicit `float` annotations (module `evap_model`).
Set all options (in alphabetical order) to their default or testing-specific values before running the doctests of a new module (script `run_doctests`).
Remove a `type: ignore` comment from function `getattr_` not required since Mypy 1.6.
Fix a few submodel type annotations in module `evap_models`.
Fix the Latex equation of method `Return_Evaporation_PenmanMonteith_V1` of the `evap` base model.
Change the unit of the fixed `evap` parameter `HeatCapacitiyAir` from WT/kg/K to J/kg/K for comprehensibility.
Add the `ignore_errors` flag to method `update_parameters` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` and to method `update` of class `Parameters` of module `parametertools` for testing purposes.
Merge the classes `Sub_ETModel_V1`, `Sub_PETModel_V1`, and `Sub_AETModel_v1` into `Sub_ETModel` for simplicity (module `evap_model`).
Avoid unnecessary calculations in method `Return_AdjustedWindSpeed_V1` of base model `evap` when the measuring and target heights are identical.
Support referencing the individual integration tests of application model `evap_morsim` and plot the results of those tests focusing on hourly step size.
Add the `PETModel_V2` interface to module `petinterfaces`.

Add the submodel `evap_pet_ambav1`, which is based on the AMBAV 1.0 model and follows `PETModel_V2` submodel interface, to the HydPy-Evap model family, and let applications model `evap_aet_hbv96` and `evap_minhas` use the `PETModel_V2` submodel interface.

Add the method `prepare_plant` to the `AETModel_V1` interface defined in module `aetinterfaces`.

So far, no actual evapotranspiration submodel uses the flag parameter `Plant`.  Nevertheless, we implement this method to ensure actual evapotranspiration submodels can pass this information to their potential evapotranspiration submodels.  Is this good practice?

Simplify the sharing mechanism between main models and sub-submodels by allowing to pass data for all interface methods.

Previously, this mechanism worked only for the so-called "predefined methods", which was too inflexible.
Fix method `Calc_ActualSurfaceResistance_V2` of application model `evap_pet_ambav1` for land use type `BODEN` (unvegetated soil).
Update the GitHub Releases token in `appveyor.xml`.
Set black's `skip-magic-trailing-comma` option to true to increase code format consistency.
Support Python 3.12 and drop Python 3.8.
Update the line lengths of module `auxfiletools`.

Use `RuntimeError` (or `AttributeNotReady`) instead of `AttributeError` at a few places and add ellipsis markes to some doctests which show attribute error messages.

The ellipsis markers are a stopgap to let the tests also pass under Python 3.12, which adds ". Did you mean ..." suggestions.  Not using `AttributeError` at the modified places is a good idea anyway.
Adjust the doctest of function `make_abc_testable` of module `testtools` to also pass under Python 3.12, which comes with an improved "Can't instantiate abstract class..." error message.
Do not use the generic type aliases from module `typing` anymore, which are deprecated since Python 3.9, as well as `Hashable` and `Sized`, which are deprecated since Python 3.12.

Let function `_number_of_line` of module `autodoctools` return zero for members without `__dict__`.

Since Python 3.12, instances of `TypeVar` and other typing features do not define the member `__dict__`, and I currently have no idea how to detect their definition lines. The returned integer is just for sorting, so possibly zero is okay, as one usually expects definitions of things like type variables at the top of a module.

Add control parameters `GL` (ground level) and `BL` (channel bottom level) to base model `wland` and its application models and turn `CD` (channel depth) into a derived parameter.

This change aims to make the parametrisation of `wland` more descriptive when coupling it to other models in a manner where differences in elevation are relevant.
Use explicit `float` annotations instead of `d_` prefixes for the method internal type declarations of base model `wland`.

Fix the Brauer et al. (2014) citation.

Now, we cite the "model development" article instead of a "model application" article.

For base model `exch` and application model `exch_v001`, rename the receiver sequence `L` to `WaterLevels`, the factor sequence`WaterLevel` to `WaterLevels`, the log sequence`LoggedWaterLevel` to `LoggedWaterLevels`, and the outlet sequence `E` to `Exchange``.
Add the `DischargeModel_V1` and the `DischargeModel_V2` submodel interface to the new module `dischargeinterfaces`.
Add base model `q` and its first application model `q_walrus`, which follows the `DischargeModel_V2` interface.
Let the application models `wland_v001` and `wland_v001` use the new `DischargeModel_V2` submodel interface (and, in their integration tests, the concrete submodel `q_walrus`).
Add the `WaterlevelModel_V1` submodel interface to module `stateinterfaces`.
Add the submodel `exch_waterlevel`, which follows the `WaterLevelModel_V1` interface.
Let the application models `wland_v001` and `wland_v001` use the new `WaterLevelModel_V1` submodel interface (and, in their integration tests, the concrete submodel `exch_waterlevel`).

Let method property `methodorder` of class `HydPy` of module `hydpytools` always include the model methods `update_senders` and `update_receivers`.

I think I added the if clauses for (likely minor) performance improvements.  But we now have the first good reason always to include these methods (see method `Pick_HS_V1` of base model `wland`, which sets`DHS` to zero in the absence of receiver node), so removing them seems justified.

Let property `sequences` of class `PyxWriter` of module `modelutils` support models without any sequences.

We just implemented the first "function-like", sequence-less submodel `q_walrus`.  This commit is a strictly required change to allow its cythonization.
Fix method `get_readerwriterinsertion` of class `XSDWriter` of module `xmltools` for models without writeable sequences (like the newly introduced `exch_waterlevel` submodel).

Add explicit `__bool__` methods to class `SubVariables` of module `variabletools`, class `Parameters` of module `parametertools`, and class `Sequences` of module `sequencetools` for a slight performance improvement.
Do not try to link `sys.stdout` in the online documentation anymore (it does not work under Python 3.12).
Fix method `save_controls` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` for handling multiple submodels with different "prepare methods" (see issue #125).
Let method `add_dischargemodel_v2` of class `Main_DischargeModel_V2` of base model `wland` update the derived parameter `CD` automatically, if possible (see issue #125).
Adjust a doctest of method `validate_xml` of class `XMLInterface` of module `xmltools` to the modified output of xmlschema 3.0.
Fix a substitution in the docstring of class `WaterLevel` of base model `exch` (completes 2c84f690e90981ea6d2b8c9861299e02f45ff717).
Silence some misleading Mypy `unreachable` warnings in property `name2submethodnames_automethod` of class `PyxWriter` of module `modelutils` (see https://github.com/python/typeshed/issues/11200).

Merge the two `PETModel_V1` interface usages `petmodel` and `petmodel` of base model `wland` and its application models into one.

 * Merge method `Calc_PE_V1` into `Calc_PET_V1` and method `Calc_PE_PETModel_V1` into `Calc_PET_PETModel_V1`.
 * Remove the `pemodel` attributes and the related functionalities from all `W` models.
 * Turn the derived parameter `AT` into a control parameter and remove the control parameters `AL` and `AS_`.
 * Increase the minimum number of hydrological response units to one (because a surface water storage must always exist).
 * Add the land type constant `WATER` to represent the surface water storage.
 * Add the land type constant `WATER` to represent the surface water storage.
 * Make sure (only) the last unit is always the surface water storage (via parameter `LT`).
 * Remove the flux sequence `PE`.
 * Add the derived parameter `NUL` to always have the number of land-related hydrological response units directly available.
 * Adjust the `update` methods and docstrings of all affected derived parameters.
 * Adjust (nearly all) model methods to the above changes.
 * Adjust the check_waterbalance method.
 * Adjust the application models `wland_v001` and `wland_v002`.
 * Add suitable masks (`Land`, `Water`, `Sealed`, and `Soil`) and let the related parameters and sequences use them.

Allow the application models `wland_v001` and `wland_v002` using submodels that comply with `PETModel_V2` interface like `evap_pet_ambav1`.

 * Complement the flux sequence `PET` with flux sequence `PE`.
 * Add method `prepare_tree` to the `PETModel_V2` submodel interface.
 * Add `add_petmodel_v2` methods to `wland_v001` and `wland_v002`.
 * Let `wland_v001` and `wland_v002` follow the `Sub_SnowCoverModel_V1` submodel interface.
 * Add and use method `Calc_PE_PET_PETModel_V2.
 * Extend method `Calc_ETV_V1` to cope with different values for potential interception evaporation and potential soil evapotranspiration.

Turn the radiation-related submodels `meteo_v001`, `meteo_v002`, `meteo_v003`, and `meteo_v004` into real submodels, add `meteo_glob_io`, `meteo_clear_glob_io`, and `meteo_psun_sun_glob_io`, enable all potential main models to use these submodels, and support the "sharing" of submodel instances between different main model instances.

 * Add the "real" submodel interface `RadiationModel_V1` for providing sunshine duration, possible sunshine duration, clear sky solar radiation, and global radiation.
 * Add the "getter" submodel interface `RadiationModel_V2` for providing global radiation
 * Add the "getter" submodel interface `RadiationModel_V3` for providing clear-sky and global radiation
 * Add the "getter" submodel interface `RadiationModel_V4` for providing potential sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation
 * Turn the `evap` input sequences `PossibleSunshineDuration` and `SunshineDuration` into factor sequences and `ClearSkySolarRadiation` and `GlobalRadiation` into flux sequences.
 * Add class `Main_RadiationModel_V1` as a base class for evap models that use radiation-like meteo submodels.
 * Derive all radiation-like meteo models from the `RadiationModel_V1` submodel interface.
 * Add method 'Process_Radiation_V1` to the `meteo` base model and let all its radiation-related submodels use it.
 * Add class `Main_RadiationModel_V2` as a base class for evap models that use radiation-like meteo submodels to gain global radiation data.
 * Add the io submodel `meteo_glob_io` for reading global radiation data.
 * Let application model `evap_tw2002` query global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V!` or `RadiationModel_V2` interface.
 * Add class `Main_RadiationModel_V3` as a base class for evap models that use radiation-like meteo submodels to gain clear-sky solar radiation and global radiation data.
 * Add the io submodel `meteo_clear_glob_io` for reading clear-sky solar radiation and global radiation data.
 * Let application model `evap_fao56` query clear-sky and global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V1` or `RadiationModel_V3` interface.
 * Add class `Main_RadiationModel_V4` as a base class for evap models that use radiation-like meteo submodels to gain possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation data.
 * Add the io submodel `meteo_psun_sun_glob_io` for reading possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation data.
 * Let application model `evap_morsim` query possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V!` or `RadiationModel_V4` interface.
 * Let application model `evap_pet_ambav1` query possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V1` or `RadiationModel_V4` interface.
 * Turn the `lland` input sequences `PossibleSunshineDuration` and `SunshineDuration` into factor sequences and `GlobalRadiation` into a flux sequence.
 * Let application model `lland_v3` query possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V1` or `RadiationModel_V4` interface.
 * Let application model `lland_v4` query possible sunshine duration, actual sunshine duration, and global radiation from a submodel that follows the `RadiationModel_V1` or `RadiationModel_V4` interface.
 * Add class `ReusableMethod` to module `modeltools`.
 * Add class `SharableModelInterface` to module `modeltools`.
 * Add method `Adjust_ClearSkySolarRadation` to base model `meteo` and use it to let its application models `meteo_v003` and `meteo_v004` calculate clear sky solar radiation (so that they implement the `RadiationModel_V1` interface completely).
 * Extend class `SubmodelAdder` of module `importtools` to handle sharable models.
 * Implement the `reset_reuseflag` mechanism into the model cythonization process.
 *  Support writing control files of models with shared submodels.
Adjust function `_get_pandasindex` of module `devicetools` slightly to adjust a deprecation warning raised by pandas 2.2.
When executing the doctests, filter out a deprecation warning caused by pandas 2.2.0 using `datetime.datetime.utcfromtimestamp` (script `run_doctests`).
Homogenise the indentation of the generated Cython source code of user-defined `CallbackParameter` functions (module `modelutils`).
Add the `repeat_sharedmodels` option to method `find_submodels` of class `Model` of module `modeltools` to avoid many (but not all) duplicate method calls.
Adjust the code style to black 24.1.

When caching the byte code of a control file, pass function `compile` the absolute file path instead of the filename so that `inspect.getsource` can find it later (method  `read2dict` of class `ControlManager` of class `filetools`).

This change fixes 7cc01e89a3af5bc2121d7a6a3b6dea1986ffe0a0, which caused problems when the special functionalities of `CallableParameter`.
